  .modal-body
    #application_arrownav_page_1.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_1
        .set-1a
          %h2 Users
          %p Access the map and find users.
        .set-1b
          %h2 Roulette
          %p Access the map and find users.
        .set-1c
          %h2 Help
          %p Click the help button on any page to be reminded of how to use a particular feature of the site
        .set-1d
          %h2 Feedback
          %p Help us improve the site
        .set-1e
          %h2 Notifications
          %p Review and learn from case feedback sent to you
        .set-1f
          %h2 Profile Menu
          %ul
            %li Basic stats and a overview of your case interview performance to-date
            %li Edit your profile
            %li Logout

    #application_arrownav_page_2.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_2
        .set-2a
          %h1 User panel
          %p Find candidates who live/work near you - click on their map markers to see their status, then send them a case partner request
          %p Browse and search for users from all over the world
          %p Select 'contacts' to see your case partners
          %p Click on their name to see their profile
        .set-2b
          %p Pull-down menu at the top to browse cities/countries where there are other candidates around the worldwhat you have in common and why you wish to work together
        .set-2c
          %h1 User Profile
          %p When two users approve each other as case partners, they can send messages and feedback to each other at anytime
          %p When you send a case partner request, sell yourself, explain ...

    #application_arrownav_page_3.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_3
        .set-3a
          %h2 Roulette
          %p Click the 'connect' button to join the 'roulette'
          %p You are now visible as 'online' to all other users on the roulette page
          %p Sit back, relax and wait for other users to look at your status and send you roulette requests
        .set-3b
          %p When another user sends you a request, a popup will appear on your screen, showing the other user's status and their Skype address, for you to call them and start a case, if you wish
          %p Alternatively browse for other users in the list, and send them a request yourself
        .set-3c
          %p
            The other users are likely not case partners of you yet, so as a security measure, to send them feedback when you are the 'interviewer' in the practise case, ask the interviewee for their 'roulette token', a random code generated every time you visit the page shown at the top.
            %br Enter their code into your roulette window to be taken to a feedback form for them

    #application_arrownav_page_4.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_4
        .set-4a
          %p Feedback system carefully designed by a consultant at one of the top 3 firms with many years of interviewing experience
        .set-4b
          %p Enter your Top 3 recommendations, specifying what you thought they need to prioritise in their preparation
        .set-4c
          %p The three main criteria Business Analytics, Interperonsal and Structure and their sub-criteria represent the areas on which candidates most often fail
        .set-4d
          %p To see more instructions on how to mark these criteria move your mouse over a sub-criteria's name
        .set-4e
          %p Move sliders to give a user a score between 1-10 for each sub-criteria - you are required to give a score on each.
          %p The sub-scriteria scores are aggregated to an average score for the main criteria
        .set-4f
          %p Enter your comments in the text boxes on the right for each criteria

    #application_arrownav_page_5.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_6
        .set-6a
          %h2 Your Progress
          %p Statistics calculated from your feedback from other users
          %p Browse and search for cases you've done in the list on the left.
        .set-6b
          %p
            Clicking on a case brings up the record for it,
            %br
              showing graphs of your scores,
              %br
                and the comments made by the interviewer.

    #application_arrownav_page_6.arrownav_page
      #modal_help_page_5
        .set-5a
          %h2 So this is just a bit of fun...
        .set-5b
          %h2 The Progress Chart
          %p Shows your aggregated scores for the three categories over time
        .set-5c
          %h2 Radar Chart
          %p In the bottom left shows your scores for your first and last case, as well as your overall average, against the different scoring criteria - look for things you are consistenly weak at to improve


  .modal-footer
    %a.btn.pull-right{"data-dismiss" => "modal", href: "#"} Close